  BeautifulSoup Par rapport √† urlopen, on n&rsquo;a pas besoin d&rsquo;appeler read pour acc√©der au contenu de page web.
Il est √† noter que la deuxi√®me option lors de la cr√©ation d&rsquo;un objet BeautifulSoup pr√©cise le parseur qui est 'html.parser' dans notre cas.
A sa place, le parseur lxml montre plus d&rsquo;avantage que html.parser dans le sens o√π il fonctionne mieux face aux HTML codes mal form√©s tels que des balises non ferm√©es, mal imbriqu√©es ou oubl√©es. De plus, il est plus rapide que l&rsquo;autre m√™me si la vitesse n&rsquo;est pas forc√©ment un avantage dans web scraping car le plus important goulet serait souvent la vitesse du r√©seau elle-m√™me.
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup html = urlopen('http://www.pythonscraping.com/pages/page1.html') bs = BeautifulSoup(html.read(), 'html.parser') print(bs.h1)  &lt;h1&gt;An Interesting Title&lt;/h1&gt;  M√™me output avec diff√©rentes expressions html = urlopen('http://www.pythonscraping.com/pages/page1.html') bs = BeautifulSoup(html, 'html.parser')   Expression 1
print(bs.h1)  Expression 2
print(bs.html.h1)  Expression 3
print(bs.html.body.h1)  Expression 4
print(bs.body.h1)   G√©rer l&rsquo;erreur d&rsquo;adresse de page Web L&rsquo;erreur HTTP peut √™tre &ldquo;404 Page Not Found&rdquo;, &ldquo;500 Internal Server Error&rdquo;, etc.
from urllib.error import HTTPError from urllib.error import URLError try: html = urlopen(&quot;http://www.pythonscraping.com/pages/page1.html22&quot;) except HTTPError as e: # this is actually a more layman understanding of URLError. HTTPError is a predefined name so that you can't replace it with other names print(e) except URLError as e: print(&quot;The server could not be found!&quot;) # the server error means there is no such website as This HTTP error may be ‚Äú404 Page Not Found,‚Äù ‚Äú500 Internal Server Error,‚Äù and so forth else: print(html.read())  HTTP Error 404: Not Found  Ecrire une fonction pour l&rsquo;erreur url def getTitle(url): try: html = urlopen(url) except HTTPError as e: return None try: bsObj = BeautifulSoup(html.read(), &quot;lxml&quot;) title = bsObj.body.h1 except AttributeError as e: return None return title # check if an element is none title = getTitle(&quot;http://www.pythonscraping.com/pages/page1.html&quot;) if title == None: print(&quot;Title could not be found&quot;) else: print(title)  &lt;h1&gt;An Interesting Title&lt;/h1&gt;
